WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:01.940
What happened?

00:01.940 --> 00:04.440
The babysitter called?

00:04.440 --> 00:07.080
His daughter is sick.

00:07.080 --> 00:10.720
What's wrong?

00:10.720 --> 00:17.860
I think she has a stomach.

00:17.860 --> 00:20.320
I'm not sure.

00:20.320 --> 00:21.760
I'm not sure.

00:21.760 --> 00:22.960
I'm not sure.

00:22.960 --> 00:23.960
I'm not sure.

00:23.960 --> 00:24.960
I'm not sure.

00:24.960 --> 00:25.960
I'm not sure.

00:25.960 --> 00:26.960
I'm not sure.

00:26.960 --> 00:27.960
I'm not sure.

00:27.960 --> 00:28.960
I'm not sure.

00:28.960 --> 00:29.960
I'm not sure.

00:29.960 --> 00:33.400
I'm a geek.

00:33.400 --> 00:34.400
He's a good father.

00:38.200 --> 00:42.080
So what do you think of him?

00:42.080 --> 00:44.120
He's very nice.

00:44.120 --> 00:46.840
But I think he was nervous tonight.

00:46.840 --> 00:49.160
It was his first date in two years.

00:52.320 --> 00:54.480
Will you see him again?

00:54.480 --> 00:55.160
I hope so.

00:55.160 --> 01:00.600
This food is delicious.

01:00.600 --> 01:05.120
He didn't get a thing to eat.

01:05.120 --> 01:07.720
You ordered enough for three or four people.

01:07.720 --> 01:09.760
But I'm not complaining.

01:09.760 --> 01:13.360
Food is delicious.

01:13.360 --> 01:14.960
Who is that?

01:14.960 --> 01:16.480
Do you think it's?

01:16.480 --> 01:17.320
No.

01:17.880 --> 01:25.560
You won't believe it, Marilyn.

01:25.560 --> 01:26.800
I believe it?

01:26.800 --> 01:27.800
Even without looking.

01:30.800 --> 01:31.960
Hi.

01:31.960 --> 01:32.880
How?

01:32.880 --> 01:35.920
Your downstairs neighbor let me in.

01:35.920 --> 01:37.080
Did you go home?

01:37.080 --> 01:38.520
I did, but everything is OK.

01:38.520 --> 01:43.880
So I decided to come back to apologize for leaving so early.

01:43.880 --> 01:46.040
I brought you a little gift.

01:46.080 --> 01:48.920
It's a bone-side tree for your new apartment.

01:48.920 --> 01:49.720
Hi, Marilyn.

01:49.720 --> 01:51.080
I hope it's not too late.

01:51.080 --> 01:51.800
Oh, not at all.

01:51.800 --> 01:53.520
We're still eating.

01:53.520 --> 01:54.960
Please come in.

01:54.960 --> 01:56.520
Join us.

01:56.520 --> 02:00.280
It's our meal from the restaurant.

02:00.280 --> 02:02.520
And how is your daughter?

02:02.520 --> 02:03.040
Oh, she's fine.

02:03.040 --> 02:05.120
It was only a tummy ache.

02:05.120 --> 02:07.360
It's good that you went back.

02:07.360 --> 02:09.960
Yes, I think it's important for me

02:09.960 --> 02:12.480
to be there since her mother died.

02:12.480 --> 02:14.680
I agree.

02:14.680 --> 02:17.160
Aren't you hungry?

02:17.160 --> 02:20.440
As a matter of fact, I am hungry.

02:20.440 --> 02:23.640
There's lots of food left.

02:23.640 --> 02:24.920
Mm.

02:24.920 --> 02:26.320
This is delicious.

02:26.320 --> 02:27.680
Enjoy.

02:27.680 --> 02:29.800
I'm going to excuse myself.

02:29.800 --> 02:33.920
I have a lot of work to do to get ready for tomorrow.

02:33.920 --> 02:34.800
Good night, Harry.

02:34.800 --> 02:35.640
It was nice meeting you.

02:35.640 --> 02:36.920
Bye, Marilyn.

02:36.920 --> 02:38.200
Good night, Susan.

02:38.200 --> 02:41.520
Good night, Marilyn.

02:41.520 --> 02:44.800
She's going to a fashion show here in the city tomorrow.

02:44.800 --> 02:47.800
She's sleeping here so she won't have to travel from Riverdale

02:47.800 --> 02:49.120
in the morning.

02:49.120 --> 02:51.840
You two must be close.

02:51.840 --> 02:52.960
We are.

02:52.960 --> 02:56.360
The whole Stuart family is close.

02:56.360 --> 02:56.920
I like that.

02:56.920 --> 03:11.480
And then two years ago, my wife died.

03:11.480 --> 03:14.040
You miss her.

03:14.040 --> 03:21.040
I do, yes, but I have Michelle and with time.

03:21.040 --> 03:25.200
Is there anyone else in your life?

03:25.200 --> 03:28.520
No, not yet.

03:28.520 --> 03:30.560
What about you?

03:30.560 --> 03:35.840
Oh, I did occasionally, but my work keeps me busy.

03:35.840 --> 03:37.560
Speaking of keeping busy, I haven't really

03:37.560 --> 03:42.080
started tomorrow, and the babysitter has to get home.

03:42.080 --> 03:43.880
Where did the time go?

03:43.880 --> 03:44.520
It's midnight.

03:49.720 --> 03:51.000
Thank you, Susan.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.680
I had a nice evening.

03:53.680 --> 03:54.520
Me too, Harry.

04:02.920 --> 04:04.800
Harry.

04:04.800 --> 04:06.400
Yes.

04:06.400 --> 04:09.920
I like to meet your daughter someday.

04:09.920 --> 04:10.880
I did.

04:10.880 --> 04:13.000
Does that mean that I can see you again?

04:13.000 --> 04:13.960
Oh, chorus.

04:13.960 --> 04:14.960
Wonderful.

04:14.960 --> 04:17.040
I'll call you when we'll go out to dinner.

04:17.040 --> 04:17.640
Please do.

04:17.640 --> 04:20.040
I promise I won't leave early.

04:20.040 --> 04:21.880
It was for a good reason.

04:23.680 --> 04:25.280
You know something?

04:25.280 --> 04:26.160
What?

04:26.160 --> 04:29.760
I think we're going to be good friends.

04:29.760 --> 04:31.360
Good night, Susan.

04:31.360 --> 04:32.400
Good night, Harry.

04:32.400 --> 04:33.520
Have a safe trip home.

04:42.640 --> 04:45.200
Are you all right?

04:45.200 --> 04:47.200
Sorry.

04:47.200 --> 04:49.360
I never liked that umbrella, Stephen.

04:49.360 --> 04:52.560
Good night, Harry.

